  Privacy Policy for DeskMat                                                                       
                                                                                                   
  Last updated: April 9, 2026                                                                      
                                                                                                   
  DeskMat ("the app") is a macOS application developed by John Kinghorn. This policy explains what 
  data the app uses and how it is handled.
                                                                                                   
  Data Collected                                                                                   
   
  Location (Weather Widget)                                                                        
                                                            
  If you use the weather widget, the app stores a latitude and longitude coordinate locally on your
   device to fetch weather data. This coordinate is saved in the app's preferences and is never
  transmitted to any server controlled by the developer.                                           
                                                            
  Weather data is fetched from a third-party weather API using your stored coordinates. Please     
  refer to that service's privacy policy for details on how they handle request data.
                                                                                                   
  Stock Ticker Symbols                                      

  If you use the stock widget, the ticker symbols you enter are stored locally on your device and  
  used to fetch market data from a third-party financial data service. These symbols are not
  transmitted to any server controlled by the developer.                                           
                                                            
  App Icons & Shortcuts                                                                            
   
  Icons and shortcuts you add to your dock are stored locally on your device only. This data never 
  leaves your Mac.                                          
                                                                                                   
  Data Not Collected                                        

  - No account or sign-in is required                                                              
  - No analytics or crash reporting data is collected
  - No advertising identifiers are used                                                            
  - No personal information is shared with or sold to third parties                                
   
  Purchases                                                                                        
                                                            
  DeskMat Pro is a one-time in-app purchase processed entirely by Apple through the App Store. The 
  developer does not have access to your payment information. Purchase records are managed by Apple
   and tied to your Apple ID. See https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy/ for details.                
                                                            
  Data Storage                                                                                     
   
  All app data (preferences, shortcuts, cached icons, location coordinates) is stored locally on   
  your device using macOS standard storage mechanisms. No data is stored on external servers
  controlled by the developer.                                                                     
                                                            
  Children's Privacy

  DeskMat does not knowingly collect any data from children under 13.                              
   
  Changes to This Policy                                                                           
                                                            
  If this policy changes materially, the updated policy will be posted at this URL with a revised  
  date.
                                                                                                   
